Describe a law on environmental protection your country should have
- what it is
- how you first learned about it
- who benefits from it
- explain who you feel about this law

I’d like to talk about an environmental law that I believe should be introduced in Vietnam, which is a strict anti-littering law.

I first learned about this type of law through Singapore, which is widely known for its cleanliness. Although I haven’t visited the country myself, several of my friends have been there and were very impressed by how clean the streets were. This made me curious, so I did some research and discovered that one of the key reasons behind this is their strict enforcement of anti-littering regulations.

Under this law, anyone caught littering, regardless of whether they are locals or tourists, is subject to heavy fines, and in more serious cases, even community service or short-term imprisonment. As a result, people are much more conscious of their behavior in public spaces.

I believe this law would benefit everyone, including local residents, tourists, and the environment as a whole. In Vietnam, littering is still quite common in public places and even in natural areas such as rivers and beaches, which leads to serious environmental problems, including water pollution and harm to marine life.

Personally, I strongly support the implementation of this law. I think it would not only improve the cleanliness of our cities but also raise public awareness about environmental responsibility. In the long run, it could significantly enhance the quality of life and make Vietnam a more attractive destination for visitors.
